<HEADLINE>
FT  13 MAY 93 / International Capital Markets: Trading in Argentaria gets
off to a brisk start
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TOM BURNS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MADRID
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ARGENTARIA, the state-controlled Spanish banking corporation which has
issued 25 per cent of its shares on the domestic and international markets,
traded briskly on its opening day yesterday when its share price rose by
more than 11 per cent in Madrid.
The shares rose sharply from Pta3,800 to Pta4,305 before easing to Pta4,230
amid heavy trading. Analysts said the trading indicated that Argentaria had
struck a correct balance in its share price by offering a sufficient premium
to investors.
Heavy demand for Argentaria meant domestic retailers were limited to maximum
investments of little more than Pta280,000 (Dollars 2,370) against the
original Pta8m limit outlined in the share offer.
