<HEADLINE>
FT  13 MAY 93 / International Company News: Prudence pays at Mitsubishi -
Financial
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHARLES LEADBEATER, MICHIYO NAKAMOTO and ROBERT THOMSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE LATE 1980s 'bubble' gave many Japanese institutions ambitions beyond
their means. Mitsubishi Bank made mistakes then but kept tighter control on
lending than most competitors.
It is expected to announce non-performing loans of Y400bn (Dollars 3.6bn) at
the end of March - about 1.3 per cent of outstanding loans and lower than
the 3 to 4 per cent at other leading institutions. Fund management returns
are higher on falling interest rates.
