FT  13 MAY 93 / International Company News: Teleglobe bounces back to the
black
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
TELEGLOBE, Canada's overseas telecommunications group, posted first-quarter
net profit of CDollars 12.2m (USDollars 9.6m) or 20 cents a share, against a
loss of CDollars 5.6m or 17 cents a year earlier, on operating revenues of
CDollars 141m, up 26 per cent.
All subsidiaries, including non-regulated units, did better and
international traffic volumes were higher. A new subsidiary, Teleglobe Cable
Systems, has been set up to develop the submarine cable operations.
Teleglobe, in which BCE, the country's biggest telecom group, has a 23 per
cent voting interest, is part of the Cantat-3 consortium building a CDollars
400m transatlantic cable due in service next year and doubling total traffic
capacity.
The group plans to tap emerging markets in eastern Europe and the CIS.
