CASCADES, the international packaging and fine paper group, has put eight
North American boxboard plants, valued at CDollars 300m (USDollars 235m), up
for sale.
The cigarette packaging and converting plants, which employ 1,250, were part
of Cascades' acquisition of Paperboard Industries in 1992.
