the entire sub-underwriting. Last week, institutions who gave firm
commitments to underwrite their allocation at roughly Pounds 6 per share
were promised additional allocations.
As a result, institutions which only last night decided they liked the terms
found themselves unable to increase their allocation. 'We would have taken
more. It's money for nothing,' said one shareholder with a 1 per cent stake
in ICI.
At the rights price, the Zeneca shares yield 5.7 per cent on the forecast
dividend of 27.5p for the year. The p/e is 13.3 historic on pro-forma
