FT  13 MAY 93 / Scargill to visit Timex picket line
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR ARTHUR Scargill, the president of the National Union of Mineworkers,
plans to visit the picket line outside the Timex factory in Dundee on Monday
to show his solidarity with workers who have been on strike there for the
past three months, Robert Taylor writes.
But his plan will be criticised tomorrow by Mr Bill Jordan, president of the
AEEU engineering union. He regards it as an unwelcome interference in a
difficult and lawful dispute that does not involve any of Mr Scargill's
members and one which will do nothing to produce a settlement.
Some members of the local Timex strike committee are also known to be
unhappy about Mr Scargill's inten-tion.
Mr Jordan will visit the Timex picket line tomorrow for the first time.
Throughout the dispute, which started in February when Timex sacked all its
manual workers for refusing to accept reduced terms and conditions as well
as a pay cut, the AEEU has sought successfully to stay strictly within the
law.
Mr Gavin Laird, the union's general secretary, warned strikers individually
that they could be dismissed from union membership if they behaved
unlawfully.
