<HEADLINE>
FT  13 MAY 93 / Court hearing on Hani killing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP and REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   JOHANNESBURG, DURBAN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Three white right-wingers accused of killing South African black leader Mr
Chris Hani appeared in court as scores of heavily armed troops ringed the
building, AP reports from Johannesburg. Mr Janusz Walus, Mr Clive
Derby-Lewis and his wife, Mrs Gaye Derby-Lewis, said nothing as a magistrate
agreed to a state request to adjourn the case to May 21.
Reuter adds from Durban: South Africa lost up to R500m (Pounds 102m) in
tourism earnings last year as a direct result of political violence, Mr Piet
van Hoven, chairman of the tourism board Satour, said yesterday.
